<DIV1 TYPE="poem">
<PB N="64" REF="000780_0064_0FAA509455F886E8">
<HEAD>A POEM. Upon the Triumphant TRANSLATION of a Mother in Our ISRAEL, <HI>Viz.</HI> Mrs. ANNE ELIOT. From <HI>This Life</HI> to a <HI>Better.</HI> on <DATE><HI>March</HI> 24<HI>th</HI> 1687.</DATE> <HI>Aetatis Suae.</HI> 84&punc;</HEAD>
<L>ALL <HI>Hallelujahs,</HI> Oh ye <HI>Heav'nly Quires,</HI></L>
<L>Ye <HI>Powers,</HI> ye Winged &amp; Immortal <HI>Fires!</HI></L>
<L>Redouble to the <HI>Highest ONE</HI>:</L>
<L>Here's Joy, to your Eternal <HI>Jubile</HI></L>
<L>Advanc'd, by th'New come welcome Company</L>
<L>Of a <HI>B<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ight Soul,</HI> but lately flown.</L>
<L>Congratulate</L>
<L>Eternally,</L>
<L>With Sacred <HI>Symphony,</HI></L>
<L>Her happy State</L>
<L><HI>Haile! <HI>Happy S<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ul</HI></HI>&punc; In Lu&s;ter excellent</L>
<L>Tran&s;cending far the <HI>Starry Firmament,</HI></L>
<L>Wh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ch is thy <HI>Foot&s;tool</HI> now become:</L>
<L>With all the World, <HI>America</HI> &s;hall Vve,</L>
<L>For to Produce thy Peer: Now ca&s;t thine Eye</L>
<L>All round about that Spacious Room,</L>
<L>None &s;halt thou &s;ee</L>
<L>Of <HI>Be&s;t Women,</HI></L>
<L>Much more <HI>Triumphant</HI> than</L>
<L>Thy &s;elf to be</L>
<L><HI>Haile!</HI> Thou <HI>Sagacious &amp; Advent'rous <HI>Soul</HI></HI>!</L>
<L>Haile, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">! Created to Controll</L>
<L><PB N="65" REF="000780_0065_0FAA509552C1E140">Weak <HI>Nature's</HI> Foes, &amp; t'take her part,</L>
<L>The <HI>King of Terrours,</HI> Thou, ('till the Com|mand</L>
<L>Irrevocable came to Stay thy Hand,)</L>
<L>Did&s;t oft <HI>Repel,</HI> by thy <HI>Choice Art</HI>:</L>
<L>By <HI>High Decree,</HI></L>
<L>Long did&s;t thou &s;tand</L>
<L>An <HI>Atlas,</HI> in <HI>Heav'n's Hand</HI></L>
<L>To th' <HI>World</HI> to be.</L>
<L><HI>All Halle<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ujahs</HI> to His bounteous <HI>Care,</HI></L>
<L>That &s;uch a <HI>Peerle&s;s <HI>Con&s;ort</HI></HI> did Prepare</L>
<L>For HIM, whom <HI>Sacred Things</HI> with<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">held</L>
<L>From <HI>Seculars</HI>; Who was to <HI>Go&s;pellize,</HI></L>
<L>And <HI>Preach Redemption</HI> to <HI>GODS Enemys</HI></L>
<L>Beyound all <HI>Memory,</HI> Rebell'd:</L>
<L>For <HI>his &s;ake,</HI> &s;ure,</L>
<L>Thine <HI>Aged Life</HI></L>
<L>It did with <HI>Death</HI> in Strife</L>
<L>So long endure.</L>
<L><HI>Heav'n's</HI> Riche&s;t Spices, Choice&s;t Graces were&punc;</L>
<L>[<HI>Queen E&s;ther</HI> like,] allotted to <HI>Thy Share,</HI></L>
<L>For to <HI>Prepare</HI> Thee for thy KING:</L>
<L>Thee, to <HI>Pay Tab<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e,</HI> for <HI>Full Recompence,</HI></L>
<L><HI>With Intere&s;t,</HI> for all thy Va&s;t <HI>Expen&s;e,</HI></L>
<L><HI>Angels,</HI> on Wings of <HI>Grace,</HI> &s;trait, bring:</L>
<L>As <HI>Pha<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">tiel,</HI></L>
<L>Thy CONSORT Dear</L>
<L>Mourning, Thee follow'th near,</L>
<L>To bid FAREWEL.</L>
<CLOSER><SIGNED>I. D.</SIGNED></CLOSER>
